By Monster Fenrick on Thursday, January 31, 2002 - 04:07 pm:

Hi Rin, burning this Durahan was the first time i had ever had any CloneCD problems, and i still don't know why I cannot get a Durahan from it.

As far as your Pandora disk problems, I would suggest several other things first:

1) Do you have MR2 and have you been succesful at burning the subcode for it?
-- (yes) ok, at least you have the burning part down)
-- (No) You may be burning the code incorrectly, if you have MR2, try burning monster codes for this as practice since the PSX seems less picky

2)The most common problem people have is they go through all the trouble of the CloneCD process and edit the image.ccd file.. when they burn the CD it gives them a Choice
Correct choice: KEEP TOC as on source, write until end of image file.
Incorrect Choice: Modify TOC to image file.

If you Modify, you have defeated the whole purpose of editing the image.ccd file.
---------------------------
I hope this helps, and maybe the information above this line should be moved to the Laboratory FAQ too, for future reference.
:)
Monster Fenrick
